# ~/.codex/AGENTS.md
# Global Codex preferences — applies to every project on this machine.
# Copy this file to ~/.codex/AGENTS.md and fill in your details.
# Project-specific rules go in ./AGENTS.md (committed to git).
# Personal project overrides go in ./AGENTS.override.md (gitignored).

## My Preferences

**Name:** _fill in_
**Role:** _fill in_ (e.g. "Full-stack developer", "iOS developer", "Non-technical founder")

**Default package manager:** _fill in_ (bun / npm / pnpm / yarn)

**Commit style:** Conventional Commits — `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`

**My shortcuts:**
- When I say "ship it" → run $ship
- When I say "check everything" → run $grill then $techdebt
- When I say "review it" → run $pr-review
- When I say "research this first" → run $research-first

**Communication style:**
- Keep explanations concise — I prefer code over prose
- Warn me before making large changes
- Always show what you're about to do before doing it

## Universal Rules (all projects)

- Always run tests before PRing
- Never hardcode secrets — use .env
- Never push to main — always use feature branches
- If something goes sideways: STOP. Ask before continuing.
- Prefer simple, readable solutions over clever ones

